aims is the basis of oppression. Noonan argues that the voices of cultural differences, when they struggle against the forces of hatred and exclusion, do not ground themselves just in the particular value of their culture but in the universal value of human freedom and self-determination.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aDifference (Philosophy)xPolitical aspects. 0aHumanism. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Humanism.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077357123540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773571235423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773571235/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles